    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1582"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1582">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/73.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>German subjects at Guadalajara, Mexico, who expect that city to be captured by
                    the Constitutionalists, have applied to the Imperial Government for assistance
                    in saving their lives and property.</p>
                <p>The Imperial Government would be especially obliged to the Government of the
                    United States if through the latter’s good offices such protection could be
                    granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
